metadata.name: Obscured by Clouds #37
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to create a painterly texture and to keep the focus on just the paint rather than any object it fills. It's coded in p5.js and uses overlapping translucent shapes to create the texture.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called 'Obscured by Clouds' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/track/3c8LKbUsjW9lMYQzVScXQT
Press 's' to save the image

Credits:
 - Technique is inspired by this essay by Tyler Hobbs: https://tylerxhobbs.com/essays/2020/how-to-hack-a-painting
 - The name of the artwork is a tribute to my favourite band

metadata.name: Digital Surface 2 #61
metadata.description:
The mechanics of Digital Surface are inspired by nature and the aesthetics by pixels. Digital Surface is an attempt to find an autonomous visual logic for a digital world made by machines.
The image is created one pixel after another, calculating the proceeding pixel based on the previous generations.
The color palettes are influenced by colors occurring in nature mixed with artificial man made colors that we see more today, aiming to look for new combinations that are pleasant to humans and natively digital.

Render time can be long, but it has been optimized from the first series and runs on average 3 times faster. Once the image is completed, press "s" to save in a small size, "m" in a medium, "l" in a large, "x" in a xlarge and "w" to save with the size of the window.

Digital Surface is a 5 series project. Each Series is released singularly, the second being Digital Surface 2. The main differentiation for series 2 is that each image contains 3 colors.
This is Francesco Forcellini Studio's first NFT project broadening their field of work from physical to digital.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.name: A Burroughs Quote #215
metadata.description:
A Burroughs Quote is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022

The birth of the Cut Up Method via the third mind. Dream Machine. Fragments. Morocco. It takes one to know one.

Esoteric rarity. Value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone.

Chrome or Firefox is recommended for your maximum viewing pleasure.

This artwork was created using p5js.

lisaorth.xyz
linktr.ee/lisaorthstudio
twitter: @lisaorthstudio

attributes.name: Word Virus
attributes.value: “The word is now a virus. The flu virus may have once been a healthy lung cell. It is now a parasitic organism that invades and damages the central nervous system. Modern man has lost the option of silence. Try halting sub-vocal speech. Try to achieve even ten seconds of inner silence. You will encounter a resisting organism that forces you to talk. That organism is the word.”
